MONEY SERVICES BUSINESS
A money services business ( MSB ) is a legal term used by financial regulators to describe businesses that transmit or convert money .
The definition was created to encompass more than just banks which normally provide these services to include non - bank financial institutions .
An MSB has specific meanings in different jurisdictions , but generally includes any business that transmits money or representatives of money , provides foreign currency exchange such as Bureaux de change , or cashes cheques or other money related instruments .
It is often used in the context of Anti Money Laundering ( AML ) legislation and rules .
